      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">BRITISH MUSEUM (NATURAL HISTORY), ¶ cromwell road, ¶ london: s.w. ¶ 1 March 1886 ¶ My dear von Mueller,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.03.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Carruthers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A39 Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (Vic. Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M: 'Answ 19/4/86, FvM'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="form%20text"
                    style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, 'Times New Roman'; ">BRITISH MUSEUM (NATURAL HISTORY),</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text"
                    style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, 'Times New Roman'; ">
                  <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">cromwell road,</seg>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text"
                    style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, 'Times New Roman'; ">
                  <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">london: s.w.</seg>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-align: end; text-indent: -0.4929in; "
               xml:lang="en">1 March 1886</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 0.4929in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.4929in; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I should have before replied to your letter<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to W. Carruthers, 21 October 1885 (in this edition as 85-10-21a).</p>
               </note> as to Forbes' Plants.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Henry Ogg Forbes.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am very glad to hear that you were able to secure so substantial a help for Forbes, and on that account, but yet more on account of the work you have already done on the Papuan Flora you have a right to claim an important part in the description of Mr Forbes' collections. There will be no difficulty in carrying out your proposals. The cellular plants we can deal with here. One of my colleagues — Mr Murray<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">George Murray.</p>
               </note> — is devoting himself to Fungi and Algae, and is able to work up whatever materials Mr Forbes may find in these Groups. I have lately had added to my staff a young man from Cambridge, Mr A. Gepp, who obtained a good position at the University, and who is devoting himself to Mosses &amp; Liverworts. I shall try to work out the Ferns. In regard to the Phanerogams my colleague Mr Ridley<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Henry Nicholas Ridley.</p>
               </note> would like to work out the <name key="Orchideae">Orchideae</name> — and indeed he would not object to the monocotyledons as a whole. He has charge of that Group in the Herbarium.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Fawcett<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">William Fawcett; see <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Proceedings</seg> of Linnean Society, London, 18 March 1886; Fawcett (1886).</p>
               </note> took a great interest in Forbes's <name key="Ericaceae">Ericaceae</name> and would be glad if he could take charge of any further specimens, and has just communicated a paper to the Linnean Soc. on <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Balanophoreae">Balanophoreae</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> &amp; <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Rafflesiaceae">Rafflesiaceae</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>, and these he would like to continue.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I fear you think I am going on rapidly to make of no effect what I allowed at the beginning, but my claims stop here.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In regard to the distribution. The whole collections will, I expect come here and be distributed by us into sets. I would take care that the second set should be sufficient for your purposes — and in any cases where uniques existed I would be prepared to send them on to you for description to be returned when you were done with them.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Of course if you would like to work up some of the monocotyledons we can easily arrange that.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In regard to Myoporums I am sorry to say we have no specimens from Forster, father or son<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to W. Carruthers, 3 December 1885, in this edition as 85-12-03a.</p>
               </note> — and only <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">M. crassifolium</hi>
               </seg> is represented in the Herb. and that by specimens collected by Anderson<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">William Anderson.</p>
               </note> at New Caledonia 1774 — the same voyage in which the Forsters were with Cooke<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Error for James Cook.</p>
               </note> — I enclose a leaf &amp; two flowers from Andersons plant. I am sorry I cannot do more.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would it be possible to secure a set of the plants of Everill's expedition up the Fly River?<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The Geographical Society of Australasia's expedition to New Guinea under Henry Charles Everill, 1885.</p>
               </note> I would very much like to have a series for the Herbarium.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust these proposals will be approved by you, &amp; am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">very sincerely yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Carruthers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
